Jackal2764: Hey aunt Jojo

The guy who came over to fix it hung out for about 10 min. We chatted about tiny lady bugs and the menagerie of the outdoors.

weird.

SO I have been in Hawaii all month long, and I have extended my stay another week. I really want to make it to the north shore of Oahu. Already I have investigated Honolulu's activities, like renting motos and traveling to Pearl Harbor, climbing Diamond Head, and exploring beaches that are so hidden that it made us nervous when Keoni (local boy) lead us to it. My friend Sovathana met Keoni on the beach, and then made arrangements for us all to hang out together. He was at most a little sketchy. So when he started taking us on this little path I thought to myself... I'm going to die and loose my wallet. It turned out that the little rocky and dangerous path lead the the most secluded beach and swimming hole. It was true paradise next to a large white palace (the only way to describe that house.) Later on Keoni stopped by our room with a hooker hiding from the police.... that's a different story. At the beach he introduced us to this really cool fisherman. Keoni borrowed his pellet gun to teach me to shoot crabs for bate. It was a real experience. Marychu, a psu student, took us to this waterfall where we swam in the water and jumped off the rocks into the natural pool. She also took us to the pali lookout where it was so windy I fell down. Sovathana and I went body boarding... and there is so much more. I really should have updated my live-journal... well I have my travel book full of good things to do.

Hehehe! I'm Jim on Ben's livejournal.

Right now Ben is at a film festival having a great time... and I'm having a great time playing on his computer.

I hope all is well in Ben land:)

I love my brother:)

"An Australian woman is suing Sydney Aquarium after a giant exhibition tank exploded, showering her with glass - and sharks."
http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/4737461.stm

It seems that I only write bad things in here. So I am not going to write anything bad. 

.......


Beach is fun, and I am tan. I miss Jane Powers and I want to go see a concert with her sometime.

My brother took me to a really great party, where we met Evan. This really cool guy, who on a side note is hot and my brother (if he was smart) would start dating. 

Jim took me on the radio the next day. 
 
Jim, Evan, and I went to this concert where I met up with Doug. 

We ended up getting food really late and then I drove home the next day.

I was pulled over by a cop. He let me off. 

The end.

EUGENE ROCKS

I have physics to do. I also have a paper and a report to work on. Ick I hate school sometimes. It can be frusterating... don't quote me on the spelling.
I stepped out of class tonight into a monsoon.
Sissyboy Idol was great! Holocene was fabulous. I got a ride home with DJ jimmyjamma and I talked to gregory. I heart him.

I have new minutes tomorrow. Yay! I have gone over my time by 6min. I am so glad that I have all those extra options for unlimited minutes. The amazing thing is that for this month I have used 1234 min. exactly and on the nose. Who did I talk to?

Sometimes you just have to make compramises. 

Tonight I was suposed to attend Cubb's b-day, but Rebecca and Elliot made dates for the Holocene. Rebecca being my only shur ride, I surrendered the b-day and went with them to the Holocene. I know they were sorry about that, but I couldn't really help that. 

I ended up at this club later that was interesting.

Tonight started when Rebar picked me up at work. 8:00 Rebar, Elliot and I then set out to see Wes' art thingy. It was at Veganopolis, which has good food... but, it made us all sick. His art work was really light hearted with strong themes; they included animals, the arctic and pirate ships. It was really beautiful work. After show and dinner we set off to see a movie which sounded like fun!... by the time we got there we felt all sick and bloaty, which is not very hot.

While there we ran into some friends, so we promptly left and drove to block buster... all bloated sick like:(. Well, we decided that it was to uncomfortable to leave the car so we ended up going to Rebecca's house where we hid from the world and relaxed, tuning into Erin Brockavitch. It was a very good film.

Things to reflect on tonight... Don't eat vegan chicken, because it is not chicken and it will probably give you vegan salmonella. 

Well goodnight peeps.

Ben may explode without warning
M

Envy idle satan? no Valentine's Day. Blah. 


I droped cookies off at lehappy for the big VD. woot! and I went to class. :( Nanny gave me a gift box of shortbread yay!

I cant get over last weekend, where I atteneded a furry party at the Pony Palace. Imagine transgenderd girls running around in bunny ears and tails. It was crazy fun. Portland is never dull. Community houses are so interesting... not overly good or bad, just interesting.  Aaron showed up randomly with a huge teddybear mask on his head. So sad things didn't work out, it would have made for an interesting relationship.

Ok, I realize today that there is hardly a night when I don't go out. Usally I don't drink, and I just watch the shows and meet people. Last night was an exception. I went out with one of my best friends. We started off, after a short cab ride, at Silverado, then we went to boxes, whisked off to the tube and then eventually ended up at CC slaughters. After the clubs we took a taxi up to vista, went down the hill to Matt's appt and then back up the hill to vista house to sleep. I got  up at 9 this morning. I feel great, just a bit tired. Well. I have home work. Fun times.

MY CLASSES ROCK! 

Weee! I just got back from the LUSH holiday party! We wen't... you gessed it! Bowlin! Wooo! And I scored a 175 in my second game. WOOO HOOO, I never left a pin standing until the 10th set when I scored a strike and then my second goround I left some pins standing.... 175! That's a kick ass score!

Ok on an even more exciting topic, I got a call from Aaron :) 

I now am about to write a letter to apply for an internship. Hopefully this good streek will keep up a couple more days.

Which David Bowie are you?

I think it fits all too well. Hehe, newyears was really fun after the family thing and driving Jim around Portland. I get to dance, drink, see a show, meet new people and visit Jane. I think Jane's house is the place to be on Newyears, it's just so crazy fun:)
